===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|NL.|Bavaria}}, from {{der|en|ML.|Baioarii||Bavarians}}, from {{der|en|la|Boiuvarii|lit=[[Boii]] settlers}}, a compound of a {{der|en|cel-gau|-}} word meaning “cattle owner” (from {{der|en|cel-pro|*bāus||cow}}) + {{der|en|gem-pro|*warjaz||settler}}. Alternatively, {{w|Julius Pokorny|Pokorny}} proposes that the first element is a word meaning “warrior”, derived from {{der|en|ine-pro|*bʰei-|*bʰei(ə)-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*bʰī-||to hit}}. This name was adopted by the [[Marcomanni]] after defeating the Boii and settling [[Bohemia]] and parts of Bavaria.

